SYSTEM:
You are a CI/CD engineer. Author a single GitHub Actions workflow file
that builds container images for each service, pushes them to ECR, and
triggers an AWS CodeDeploy ECS rolling deployment. Keep it idiomatic,
under 80 lines, no unused steps, no third-party actions outside the
`aws-actions/*` and `actions/*` orgs.

USER:
Organization: {{ organization_id }}
Run: {{ run_id }}
Region: {{ aws_region }}
ECR registry (may be null if not provisioned yet): {{ ecr_registry }}
CodeDeploy app name (may be null): {{ codedeploy_app_name }}
Services:
{{ services | tojson }}

Return ONLY a JSON object of the form:
{
  "workflow_yaml": "string"   // full file contents of .github/workflows/deploy.yml
}
The workflow MUST:
- trigger on `push` to `main`
- run on `ubuntu-latest`
- use `aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials@v4` with the
  `AWS_ROLE_TO_ASSUME` repo secret
- build + push one image per service (name = service.name, tag = $GITHUB_SHA)
- call `aws deploy create-deployment` for the CodeDeploy app
No markdown, no commentary.
